{"id":"4b6e908f-afbf-49cf-8bda-326ab12dabca","title":"SIP vs FD — कौन सा बेहतर है?","messages":[{"id":"1784131352900","role":"user","content":"SIP vs FD — कौन सा बेहतर है?"},{"id":"1784131352901","role":"assistant","content":"**💡 Quick Answer: SIP और FD दोनों के अपने फायदे हैं। SIP में ₹5,000/month invest करने से 20 साल में ~₹49.9 lakh बन सकते हैं (at 12% returns), जबकि FD में interest rate fixed होता है और ये लगभग 7-8% होता है।**\n\nSIP (Systematic Investment Plan) और FD (Fixed Deposit) दोनों ही popular investment options हैं, लेकिन इनके अपने फायदे और नुकसान हैं।\n\n### SIP के फायदे:\n1. **Higher Returns Potential**: SIP में equity mutual funds में invest किया जाता है, जहां returns 12-15% तक हो सकते हैं long-term में।\n2. **Rupee Cost Averaging**: SIP में हर महीने fixed amount invest होती है, जिससे आप कम price पर ज्यादा units और ज्यादा price पर कम units खरीदते हैं।\n3. **Power of Compounding**: Long-term में SIP का compounding effect बहुत powerful होता है।\n\n### FD के फायदे:\n1. **Guaranteed Returns**: FD में आपको fixed interest rate मिलता है, जो आमतौर पर 7-8% per annum होता है।\n2. **Low Risk**: FD पूरी तरह से risk-free होता है, क्योंकि ये banks द्वारा backed होता है।\n3. **Liquidity**: कुछ FD schemes में premature withdrawal की सुविधा भी होती है।\n\n### Comparison Table:\n| Feature | SIP | FD |\n|---------|-----|----|\n| **Risk Level** | High (equity exposure) | Low (risk-free) |\n| **Potential Returns** | 12-15% | 7-8% |\n| **Liquidity** | Moderate (exit load applicable) | High (premature withdrawal option) |\n| **Taxation** | Capital Gains Tax | Interest income taxable |\n\n### Example:\n- SIP: ₹5,000/month invest करने पर 20 साल में **~₹49.9 lakh** बन सकते हैं (at 12% returns)।\n- FD: ₹5,000/month invest करने पर 20 साल में **~₹26.3 lakh** बन सकते हैं (at 7% returns)।\n\n```chart\n{\n  \"title\": \"SIP vs FD Returns (20 Years)\",\n  \"type\": \"bar\",\n  \"yAxisFormatter\": \"currency\",\n  \"data\": [\n    {\"name\": \"SIP (12%)\", \"value\": 4990000},\n    {\"name\": \"FD (7%)\", \"value\": 2630000}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 🎯 Key Takeaway\nSIP में higher returns की potential होती है, लेकिन इसमें risk भी होता है। FD पूरी तरह से safe है, लेकिन returns कम होते हैं।\n\n### अगला कदम:\n1. अपनी risk tolerance और financial goals को समझें।\n2. SIP और FD दोनों में invest करके diversify करें।\n3. Long-term investment horizon रखें।\n\n⚠️ Disclaimer: यह financial advice नहीं है। Investment decisions लेने से पहले certified financial advisor से consult करें।","isStreaming":false,"sources":[{"title":"AMFI India","url":"https://www.amfiindia.com/","domain":"amfiindia.com"},{"title":"MoneyCal.in","url":"https://moneycal.in","domain":"moneycal.in"}],"recommendations":[{"id":"prepayment-calculator","title":"The Sovereign Wealth Optimizer (Loan Prepayment vs Investment)","description":"Elite Debt vs. Equity Analysis tool for FY 2026-27. Compare loan prepayment interest savings against mutual fund SIP wealth generation. Make the smartest debt decision for 2026.","category":"Loan Calculators","url":"/tools/prepayment-calculator","keywords":"The Sovereign Wealth Optimizer (Loan Prepayment vs Investment) Loan Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"sip-calculator","title":"SIP Calculator","description":"Free SIP Calculator India – Systematic Investment Plan Calculator for mutual funds. Calculate SIP returns, maturity amount, and wealth creation with rupee cost averaging. Compare SIP vs lumpsum.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/sip-calculator","keywords":"SIP Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"step-down-sip-calculator","title":"Step-Down SIP Calculator","description":"Model SIP with annual decrease. Plan tapered contributions near goals or pre-retirement while keeping compounding discipline.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/step-down-sip-calculator","keywords":"Step-Down SIP Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"},{"id":"fd-calculator","title":"FD Calculator","description":"Free Fixed Deposit (FD) Calculator India. Calculate FD maturity, interest earned, and effective annual rate with monthly, quarterly, or annual compounding. Compare SBI, HDFC, ICICI rates.","category":"Investment Calculators","url":"/tools/fd-calculator","keywords":"FD Calculator Investment Calculators","type":"calculator"}],"followUpQuestions":["SIP में invest करने के लिए कौन से best mutual funds हैं?","FD interest rates में कैसे comparison करें?","Systematic Withdrawal Plan (SWP) कैसे काम करता है?"]}],"createdAt":"2026-07-15T16:03:05.093Z","updatedAt":"2026-07-15T16:14:22.616Z"}